Hub，则可以直接从移动设备运行 Android 应用程序，而无需将其安装在计算机上。通过此更新，您可以回复消息或检查午餐交付情况，而无需伸手拿手机。</p><p>该功能仍然仅限于谷歌和小米的少数支持 Android 13 的手机。您需要 Google 提供的<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-4a-review-price-specs-availability-150050960.html">Pixel 4a</a>或更高版本。与此同时，小米粉丝至少需要一台 12T。您的 Chromebook 和手机必须位于同一个 WiFi 网络上并且物理距离很近。某些网络可能不支持该功能，但如果需要，您可以使用 Chrome 操作系统的即时网络共享来建立链接。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>与测试期间一样，您不会希望将应用程序流用于游戏或其他密集型 Android 应用程序。这更多的是为了响应通知，而不是任何严肃的承诺——你仍然需要为此安装应用程序。不过，它为 Chromebook 提供了 macOS <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/windows-11-phone-link-your-phone-175356621.html">和 Windows</a>中的一些手机集成功能，并且可以帮助您在工作时保持专注。</p><p> M115 升级还允许您签署 PDF 文档并保存签名以供以后使用。谷歌还重新设计了面向键盘的快捷应用程序，提供了新的界面和更简单的应用内搜索。</p><p></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/google-rolls-out-android-app-streaming-to-chromebooks-following-beta-203014704.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/google-rolls-out-android-app-streaming-to-chromebooks-following-beta-203014704.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> a617169b-bca6-4888-a546-a35d0991990b</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jul 2023 20:30:14 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689969622</ingested><modified> 2023-07-21T20:00:27+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mobile Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/dacb0300-ef3b-11ed-a7ff-b0a51027584a" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-05/dacb0300-ef3b-11ed-a7ff-b0a51027584a" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Google]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Android app streaming in Chrome OS]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Android app streaming in Chrome OS]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Amazon is reportedly making employees relocate for return-to-office]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>据<em>彭博社</em><a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-07-21/new-york-bound-7-000-pound-weed-hauls-show-growing-black-market">采访的</a>消息人士透露，一些亚马逊员工将被迫搬迁，以履行公司要求<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-wants-employees-to-return-to-the-office-in-may-203129447.html">每周在办公室工作三天的</a>政策。受影响的人将包括受雇从事偏远岗位的工人以及在大流行高峰期间搬家的工人。</p><p>据<em>《华尔街日报》</em> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:The Wall Street Journal;elmt:;cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=2f007401-3eaa-4237-b69b-54ccbe125502&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=The+Wall+Street+Journal&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARMbkSc0DzUl9U7p1xfUre0J1INQe6M3BM_a21aTgFD5&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Famazon-asking-employees-to-return-to-main-hubs-3e2dcb89" class="rapid-with-clickid">报道</a>，远程亚马逊员工将必须向“主要中心”办公室报到，包括位于西雅图、纽约和旧金山（可能还有其他地点）的公司总部。然而，谁必须搬迁以及搬迁地点的决定将由部门决定。据报道，该公司尚未确定有多少员工将不得不离开家乡。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>亚马逊的一位代表今天告诉<em>彭博社</em>，自首席执行官安迪·贾西 (Andy Jassy) 在 2 月份宣布执行在职命令以来，亚马逊观察到“更多的活力、协作和联系正在发生”。该公司的一些员工认为该政策雪上加霜，因为该政策的出台与 2022 年底开始的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-will-lay-off-another-9000-employees-in-the-coming-weeks-152653190.html">大范围裁员</a>差不多同时进行，影响了约 27,000 名员工。五月，数百名员工<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-workers-walk-out-to-protest-return-to-office-mandates-and-the-companys-climate-impact-194937443.html">举行罢工</a>，抗议重返办公室政策和公司的<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-annual-susainability-report-2022-carbon-emissions-230707953.html">气候缺陷</a>。</p><p>亚马逊发言人告诉<em>彭博社</em>：“我们将继续寻找将更多团队聚集在同一地点的最佳方式，并且在做出影响员工的决策时，我们将直接与员工沟通。”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/amazon-is-reportedly-making-employees-relocate-for-return-to-office-200435517.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/amazon-is-reportedly-making-employees-relocate-for-return-to-office-200435517.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 64c2b19a-c9d9-42a6-bbed-5b3d1c592900</guid><dc:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jul 2023 20:04:35 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689969876</ingested><modified> 2023-07-21T20:04:40+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="3648" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-08/6a897140-e15a-11ea-ad3a-ff9c83763900" width="5472"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3648" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-08/6a897140-e15a-11ea-ad3a-ff9c83763900" width="5472"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Lisa Werner via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Amazon corporate office building in Sunnyvale, California]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Company Signs]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[OpenAI's trust and safety lead is leaving the company]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:LinkedIn;elmt:;cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=6deefbf2-941b-4156-9f41-a61ebb50d13d&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=LinkedIn&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASXXaVhmlD1rmaZpWt91xYB-wHoboCCQ3gwLvPgR8H_h&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fupdate%2Furn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7087887039756447744%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid"><ins>Linkedin 发帖宣布，OpenAI 的信任和安全主管 Dave Willner 已离职。</ins></a>威尔纳将继续担任“顾问角色”，但已要求 Linkedin 关注者“寻求”相关机会。这位前 OpenAI 项目负责人表示，此举是在决定花更多时间陪伴家人之后做出的。是的，他们总是这么说，但威尔纳用实际的细节来跟进。</p><p> “在 ChatGPT 推出后的几个月里，我发现履行诺言变得越来越困难，”他写道。 “OpenAI 正在经历一个高强度的发展阶段——我们的孩子也是如此。任何有小孩、工作强度超级大的人都会感受到这种紧张感。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>他继续表示，他对公司在他任职期间所取得的“一切成就感到自豪”，并指出这是世界上“最酷、最有趣的工作之一”。</p><p>当然，这一转变是在 OpenAI 及其标志性产品 ChatGPT 面临一些法律障碍之后发生的。美国联邦贸易委员会<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ftc-opens-investigation-into-chatgpt-creator-openai-164551958.html"><ins>最近对该公司展开调查</ins></a>，担心该公司违反了消费者保护法，并从事可能损害公众隐私和安全的“不公平或欺骗性”行为。调查确实涉及泄露用户私人数据的错误，这似乎属于信任和安全的范围。</p><p>威尔纳说，他的决定实际上是一个“相当容易做出的选择，尽管像我这样的职位的人通常不会在公开场合如此明确地做出这样的选择。”他还表示，他希望他的决定将有助于使有关工作/生活平衡的更公开的讨论正常化。</p><p>近几个月来，人们对人工智能的安全性越来越担忧，OpenAI 是应拜登总统和白宫的要求<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ai-companies-will-reportedly-commit-to-safeguards-at-the-white-houses-request-185646283.html"><ins>同意对其产品采取某些保障措施</ins></a>的公司之一。其中包括允许独立专家访问代码、标记偏见等社会风险、与政府共享安全信息以及对音频和视频内容加水印，让人们知道它是人工智能生成的。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/openais-trust-and-safety-lead-is-leaving-the-company-190049987.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/openais-trust-and-safety-lead-is-leaving-the-company-190049987.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 9f9d1c44-392d-48ae-9630-c5f919e39172</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jul 2023 19:00:49 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689964201</ingested><modified> 2023-07-21T18:30:05+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="2892" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/c2bad2a0-27ed-11ee-a8fb-34c9396d09ee" width="4338"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2892" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/c2bad2a0-27ed-11ee-a8fb-34c9396d09ee" width="4338"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[FILE - The OpenAI logo is seen on a mobile phone in front of 